"adj. 嗅觉的 【英】 adj. 嗅觉的(of the sense of smell) 【记】 ol(=smell味)+fact( 做)+ory→做出味道来 →嗅觉的；分割记忆：ol+factor y 【同】 派生词: olfaction (n. 嗅觉) 【例】 The nose is an olfactory organ. adj. 嗅觉的 【记】ol = oil, factory: 油场会发出气味－嗅觉的 【参】ointment(n 油膏; 润肤用品)oint = oiloligarchy(n 寡头政治)oli = oil, arch统治－石油业是少数人的统治 【记】ol- (源自odor) + factory 工厂，人体能辨别气味的工厂就是嗅觉器官；oil 油 + factory　油厂，到了油厂明显的感觉是嗅觉，嗅到汽油味 olfactory (adj.)  1650s, from Latin olfactorius, from olfact-, past participle stem of olfacere ""to get the smell of, sniff,"" from olere ""emit a smell, give off a smell of"" (see odor) + facere ""make"" (see factitious)."
